Regular seeds usually contain 55% to 65% of female seeds. In order to make sinsemilla marijuana, the male and female plants need to be separated before flowering time. This requires knowledge of how to recognize the genders in order to separate them. The plant's gender can be determined at the beginning of the flowering stage.
